# YetiMatch - Flutter Project

## Project Structure
- Package: com.daddoodev.yetimatch
- Targets: Android, iOS, Linux (desktop)
- Shared code in `lib/` (Dart)
- UI: Flutter with Material 3

## Architecture
- Screens in `lib/screens/`, app shell in `lib/app/`
- State: setState at root or ChangeNotifier where needed; no KMP ViewModels/StateFlow
- Platform-specific code: `dart:io` Platform checks or conditional imports; no expect/actual

## Best Practices
- Use Dart SDK and pub.dev packages; prefer cross-platform packages
- JSON: dart:convert or packages (e.g. json_serializable) as used in project
- Async: async/await and Future; networking via `http` or project choice
- Resources: `assets/` in project root; declare in `pubspec.yaml` under `flutter.assets`

## UI and Theming
- Material 3: MaterialTheme, Scaffold, AppBar, Button, Card, etc.
- Theme in `lib/theme/app_theme.dart`: yetiMatchTheme(dark: bool), themeMode (Light/Dark/System)
- Use Theme.of(context).colorScheme and Theme.of(context).textTheme; no hard-coded colors in screens

## Dependencies
- Manage in `pubspec.yaml`; use Flutter/Dart packages from pub.dev
- Firebase (mobile), REST auth/Firestore for desktop where SDK isn’t available

